[
    {
        "source_sentence": "請賓頭盧法",
        "translation": "inviting Piṇḍola to perform a ritual",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b04_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "宋沙門釋慧簡譯",
        "translation": "Song Dynasty Master Shi Hui Jian Translation",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b06_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "天竺國有優婆塞國王長者。",
        "translation": "\"In India, there was an elder from the kingdom of Upāsaka.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b07_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "若設一切會。",
        "translation": "If he set up any assembly, he would always invite Piṇḍola, the word for arhat, to vow.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b07_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "常請賓頭盧頗羅墮誓阿羅漢賓頭盧者字也。",
        "translation": "He would always invite Piṇḍola and Bhāradvāja to come. Piṇḍola is a word.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b07_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "頗羅墮誓者姓也。",
        "translation": "\"Bāladhārāja\" is a surname.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b09_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "其人為樹提長者現神足故。",
        "translation": "That man was the manifestation of the spiritual powers of the elder of Jyoti.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b09_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "佛擯之不聽涅槃。",
        "translation": "The Buddha rejected him and wouldn't allow him to enter nirvāṇa.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b10_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "勅令為末法四部眾作福田。",
        "translation": "I ordered him to be a field of merit for the four groups of people in the final period.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b10_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "請時於靜處燒香禮拜。",
        "translation": "He asked them to burn incense and venerate him in a quiet place.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b11_4",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "向天竺摩梨山。",
        "translation": "He went up to Mount Mālikā in India.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b11_5",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "至心稱名言。",
        "translation": "With all his heart, he called his name and said.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b12_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "大德賓頭盧頗羅墮誓。",
        "translation": "\"Venerable Piṇḍola Pārājapati.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b12_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "受佛教勅。",
        "translation": "I've been commanded by the Buddha to do so.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b12_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "為末法人作福田。",
        "translation": "I'll be a field of merit for those in the latter stages of life.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b13_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "願受我請。",
        "translation": "Please accept my invitation.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b13_4",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "於此處食。",
        "translation": "Eat here.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b13_5",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "若新作屋舍。",
        "translation": "If he builds a new house, he'll invite it.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b14_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "亦應請之言。",
        "translation": "You should also invite them, saying.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b14_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "願受我請。",
        "translation": "\"May I invite you to.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b14_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "於此舍床敷止宿。",
        "translation": "Spread out a bed in this dwelling and stay there for the night.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b14_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "若普請眾僧澡浴時。",
        "translation": "If you were to invite all the saṃgha to bathe, you should also invite them, saying.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b15_4",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "亦應請之言。",
        "translation": "You should also invite them, saying.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b15_5",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "願受我請。",
        "translation": "\"May I invite you to take a bath here?",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b16_6",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "於此洗浴。",
        "translation": "Wash and bathe them here.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b16_7",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "及未明前具香湯淨水澡豆楊枝。",
        "translation": "Before he learns, he'll prepare scented bathing water, wash beans and poplar branches.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b16_8",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "香油調和冷暖。",
        "translation": "Scented oil will mix the cold and warmth.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b17_9",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "如人浴法。",
        "translation": "Bathe like a human being.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b17_10",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "開戶請入。",
        "translation": "He opens the door and invites you to enter.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b17_11",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "然後閉戶。",
        "translation": "Then he closes the door.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b18_12",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "如人浴訖頃。",
        "translation": "After he finishes bathing like a human, the monks then enter.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b18_13",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "眾僧乃入。",
        "translation": "Only then do the saṃgha enter.",
        "source": "T32n1689_001:0784b18_14",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "凡會食澡浴。",
        "translation": "Whenever there's an assembly for food and bathing, it's important to invite all the saṃgha to wholeheartedly seek liberation.",
